The BVDV strains in the MLV and KV are predominantly the CP BVDV1a and BVDV2a strains (Tables 42-1
and 42-2
). A limited number of vaccines have NCP strains. Both MLV and KV vaccines induce antibodies to a wide range of BVDV strains including the three predominant subtypes in the United States: BVDV1a, 1b, and 2a.80., 141.
